Rob Griffin

I am a statistical programmer at AstraZeneca, based in Sweden, with a background in academic research. As an academic in evolutionary genetics, I used R for statistical programming for over ten years. As this became the aspect of my work I enjoyed the most, I decided to change career path to make this the mainstay of my work. I joined the AstraZeneca Graduate Program for Late Respiratory and Immunology Biometrics in 2020 where I have received training and valuable on the job experience in SAS (including proc SQL queries) and Groovy, clinical programming practices and clinical data standards (CDISC), and more general skills such as communication and leadership.

I also enjoy programming and learning new programming languages in my spare time. I am currently self-teaching Python, aim to learn some C and Java in the near future, and have used HTML, CSS and Javascript for front-end web development, RShiny for web-based applications, Java, Kotlin and XML for Android application development, and LaTeX and Pandoc to produce PDF and HTML documents integrated with RMarkdown.

My academic research was focused on the evolution of sex differences. This work relied on methods from the field of quantitative genetics, allowing the variation within and covariation between characteristics to be dissected into their genetic, environmental and other underlying components with multivariate statistical approaches. This work aimed to established whether the shared genome constrains the evolution of further sex differences, how that constraint is modified by mutation and environmental change, and the related evolutionary dynamics of sex chromosomes. You can read more in my PhD thesis and research papers.

Much of my spare time is spent with my young family - my three boys Nils, Olof and Sven and my partner. We try to spend our time enjoying the Swedish outdoors year round, with spring and summer spent exploring the forests and lakes, autumn spent picking blueberries and hunting for chanterelle mushrooms, and winter spent sledding, skiing and playing in the snow. I also spend time cycling, both road and XC, and running, and following sports including football and cricket.
